The paper deals with predicting protest participation on social media, which involves analyzing user behavior and interactions. This falls under the categories of social media analysis (cs.SI), social computing (cs.SOC), natural language processing (cs.CL), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the focus is more on social media analysis and social computing, these two categories are the most likely, followed by natural language processing, cybersecurity, and cryptography and security.
